Use GNU stow to symlink files from this directory to my home directory.

Store related dotfiles in a package. This is the stow directory. Running stow 
will symlink the dotfiles to the target directory (home directory).

ex: .bashrc
.dotfiles
├── bash
│   └── .bashrc
running "stow bash" from the .dotfiles directory will symlink .bashrc to the
home directory.

ex: init.nvim
.dotfiles
├── nvim
│   ├── .config
│       └── nvim
|   	 	└── init.vim
running "stow nvim" from the .dotfiles directory will symlink init.nvim to
~/.config/nvim/init.nvim.

[1]https://www.gnu.org/software/stow/
